This is where the error is occurring. The issue is with the isAuthenticated middleware:
javascriptCopyconst { isAuthenticated } = require('../middleware/authMiddleware');
In your middleware/authMiddleware.js file, you're not exporting the isAuthenticated function directly. Instead, you're attaching it to the global object. The import should be:
javascriptCopyconst authMiddleware = require('../middleware/authMiddleware');
const app = require('express')(); // You'll need access to the app instance
const { isAuthenticated } = authMiddleware(app);
Or better yet, pass the app instance to the routes when mounting them in server.js.
